-- India’s May Oil Refinery Output Climbs 2.9% to 14.8 Million Tons
-- B y   R a k t e e m   K a t a k e y
-- 2012-06-27T09:30:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/india-s-may-oil-refinery-output-climbs-2-9-to-14-8-million-tons.html
India ’s crude oil refineries
increased fuel production by 2.9 percent to 14.8 million metric
tons in May, the oil ministry said.  Reliance Industries Ltd. (RIL) ’s output rose 1.9 percent to 3
million tons last month, while Indian Oil Corp.’s production
fell 4.1 percent to 4.6 million tons, the ministry said in an e-
mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
